SUMMARY:Frink Ridge - Invasive Plant Removal
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Frink Park. \nWe will visit violence upon the invasive species at this job site\, removing holly\, ivy\, clematis\, and blackberry. Specifically\, we will complete a couple of survival rings\, freeing the trees of ivy that is depriving them of water and nutrients while adding significant weight to them\, risking them falling down in a wind storm. \nI always invite those who help clear areas in the spring to return in the fall to plant native plants in the area they cleared. \nRegister
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/frink-ridge-invasive-plant-removal-2/
LOCATION:WA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/home-new-2-catherine-anstett-trolls-knoll-gloves.jpg
END:VEVENT
